SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to VERA's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260325T055847Z
DTSTART:20260409T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at VERA’s screen printing studio: From hand-draw
	ing a stencil on transparency\, coating and burning a screen\, to pulling 
	your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop layout\, equipment
	\, and culture. Learn techniques for creating screens\, terminology\, and 
	more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. Students will walk away
	 with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color paper prints\, and thei
	r own print of a special Vera design\, specific to the 101 class.\n\nThis 
	class is a prerequisite for 200-level classes at VERA\, as well as access 
	to Open Sessions to work on your own projects in VERA’s screen printing st
	udio.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/Q356874d5807\n\nFrom The Vera Project
